  "title": "NC Siblings Used Family Birthdays to Win $390,000 in the Lottery",
  "script": "It paid off? Jason and Marci Lowry from Winnabow, North Carolina have been playing the lottery together for years. Every ticket, they use family birthdays for the numbers. Same routine every time. Then in December, they matched all 5 white balls in the Lucky for Life drawing. The prize: $25,000 a year for life. Or a lump sum of $390,000. They took the lump sum — split it down the middle. After taxes, each sibling walked away with $140,443. The money's going toward bills, car repairs, and fixing up the house. Nothing flashy. Just two people who kept doing the same thing week after week and finally hit. Are your family's birthdays lucky numbers?",
